{{Unreferenced stub|auto=yes|date=December 2009}}
'''George Brettingham Sowerby III''' (16 September 1843 – 31 January 1921) was a [[United Kingdom|British]] [[conchology|conchologist]], publisher, and illustrator.

He, too, worked (like his father [[George Brettingham Sowerby II]] and his grandfather [[George Brettingham Sowerby I]]) on the ''Thesaurus Conchyliorium'', a comprehensive, beautifully illustrated work on [[mollusc]]s. He was [[Colour blindness|colour blind]], and thus his daughter did most of the colouring of his engravings.

