[[File:Obruchevit-oxyyttropyrochlore.jpg|thumb|Oxyyttropyrochlore-(Y) (obruchevite)]]
'''Oxyyttropyrochlore-(Y)''',<ref>[https://www.mindat.org/min-40346.html Mindat]</ref> also referred to as "obruchevite" or "yttropyrochlore-(Y)", is a potential (not yet accepted) [[Valence (chemistry)|zero-valent-dominant]] mineral of the [[pyrochlore]] group. Its formula can be written as (Y,◻)<sub>2</sub>Nb<sub>2</sub>O<sub>2</sub>O.

The name "yttropyrochlore-(Y)" for this compound was used by Kalita (1957), and Ercit et al. (2003), but it has become obsolete and the [[mineral]] status is not yet clear. The yttropyrochlore-(Y) as mentioned by Tindle & Breaks (1998) is in fact "oxyyttropyrochlore-(Y)".

