{{Underlinked|date=December 2015}}

'''Siu Shih Chang''' (Xui Shi Zhang) (born 1918) is a [[Chinese people|Chinese]] [[Botany|botanist]] and [[plant]] collector.<ref>[http://kiki.huh.harvard.edu/databases/botanist_search.php?mode=details&id=63630]</ref> The [[elm]] species ''[[Ulmus changii]]'' was named for him after he discovered it in 1936.

==Publications==
*Chang, S. S. (1998). Cannaboideae. In: Chang Siushih & Wu Chengyih, eds., ''Fl. Reipubl. Popularis Sin.'' 23(1): 220224.
*Chang, S. S. (1989). ''Flora Guizhouensis'', Vol. 4. Spermatophyta. Sichuan Nationalities Publishing, 1989. {{ISBN|7540902604}}, {{ISBN|9787540902605}}

{{botanist|S.S.Chang|Chang}}

